The article condemns recent Houthi attacks on civilian infrastructure in Saudi Arabia, including water treatment facilities and oil and natural gas infrastructure. The attacks are said to be supported by Iran, in violation of UN resolutions. Saudi Arabia and the Yemeni Government have endorsed UN calls for ceasefires and de-escalation, but the Houthis have rejected them and continue to launch new offensives and terrorist acts. The article calls for cooperation with the UN to de-escalate the conflict and urges international support for defending against Houthi attacks.